## How Insar Works
Insar data that we view are colors on a map ranging through a spectrum of colors to represent depth on the terrain. A full cycle (red -> red) indicates 2.8cm/28mm or 1.1 inches. Spectrum is red, orange, tellow, green, blue, red, etc. 

Subsidence indicates fall in terrain, uplift indicates upwards growth in terrain.
